title: New York City: Autumn
description:
"Don't you love New York in the fall? It makes me want to buy school supplies. I would send you a bouquet of newly sharpened pencils if I knew your name and address."

New York City in the fall. Period. This is a sentence that says a million things even though it is in fact...a fragment. Because there is no place like NYC in autumn, it is perfection.
